window.bookSummaryJSON = "<p>A year has passed since the Sheridans fled the plague in England, but a new crisis tears Valerie and Louisa apart once again, with dire consequences. As the stranded Whitfields desperately try to return home to the 17th century, the Sheridans face a threat of a different nature. The past rarely stays in the past, and a shocking murder brings things to a head as Kit is accused of the crime, and shameful secrets are brought into the open.</p> <p>Meanwhile, in the 18th century, the Revolutionary War is still raging, and Finn comes face-to-face with an old enemy who won’t be outwitted again. As Finn fights for his life, Sam must face his own demons and figure out where his loyalties lie.</p> <p>Long-buried secrets, blackmail, murder, and a tender, new romance take center stage in this installment of The Hands of Time series.</p>"; 
